courses.learning_outcomes:
\* The student should be able to enhance and update his knowledge and expertise of medical laboratory professionals to cope with the ever-changing service demands;
\* The student should be able to improve his skills on critical analysis, problem solving and innovative thinking, in addition to the integration of theory and application of diagnostic laboratory techniques;
\* The student should be equipped with the necessary research skill and deliver evidence-based medical laboratory services;
\* The student should have the skills and knowledge for a good career in medical laboratory science.

The project allows the student to undertake an important piece of research activities in a topic related to the selective course of the study programme of Master of Science in Medical Laboratory Sciences in a constrained period of time. It is the key element of the programme intended to extend student’s knowledge and understanding of one particular discipline in a more in-depth level, which may not be possible by undertaking taught post-graduate courses. Besides, it provides the opportunity for the student to specialise in a particular area of study in line with the student’s career interests and aspirations. Student is expected to satisfactorily complete a basic research training and undertake a substantial piece of independent work, which is a more advanced and intensive study than a first degree, in not less than 12 months, and present a satisfactory thesis.

Upon completion of the research project, student will be able to display and demonstrate the following abilities and expertise:
• asking critical questions;
• effectively reviewing literature for likely answers to the queries;
• putting up hypotheses;
• designing vigorous testings of the conjectures;
• being competent to investigate the specific subjects;
• being able to focus on unique issues;
• undertaking independent research;
• effectively working with research collaborators and colleagues;
• complying to medical ethics and the importance of good research practice;
• meticulously analysing and evaluating research data;
• presenting information both orally and in written form to a professional standard.
